GitHub repo link: https://github.com/MartyV33/Choose-Adventure-Ruins-of-Mexico.git

Project Deployable Link: https://martyv33.github.io/Choose-Adventure-Ruins-of-Mexico/.git 

1. Game Choice: "Choose Your Own Adventure". Will be based in the Ruins of Mexico.
2. User Stories:
  1. As a user, I want to immerse myself in an intriguing storyline set in the Ancient Ruins of Mexico, where my choices impact the story.
  2. As a user, I expect meaningful choices that lead to different outcomes, creating replay value and a personalized experience.
 3. As a user, I look forward to encountering visual elements (Such as ancient art) that enhance the atmosphere and evoke the mysterious setting.
 4. As a user, I want to uncover secrets, solve puzzles, and explore divergent paths within the ruins, leading to multiple endings.

3. Storing the scenes:
   I will be using Data Structure to store the scenes. Using either an array or object to store the scenes. Using data structure, each scene can have properties like Text description, choices, and art references. 


4.   Persudocode:
